Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds (peel first if you prefer). Cut into 1cm chunks - they need to be small so they can cook quickly.

Pop the squash onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Chop the @Tenderstem broccoli{150%g} into thirds.

Pour the cold @water{300%ml} for the rice (see pantry for amount) into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati rice{150%g} and 1/4 tsp salt and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Heat a #large saucepan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @cashew nuts{25%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%mins}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer to a #bowl{}.

Pop your pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the @onion{}(as prepared) and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @North Indian style spice mix{2%tbsp}. Cook for ~{1%min}, stirring continuously.

Pour in the @water{200%ml} for the curry and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Stir to combine well.

Stir the broccoli and @diced chicken breast{260%g} into the curry, bring to a boil, then lower the heat to a simmer. Cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until the broccoli is tender and the chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> TIP: The mixture will be quite thick, so stir it occasionally to stop it from sticking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the broccoli is tender, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} until completely combined. Remove from the heat if the butternut squash hasn't finished cooking yet.

Once cooked, stir the roasted squash through the curry.

Bring back to the boil, adding a splash of water if it's a little thick, then remove from the heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}. Top with the curry and sprinkle with the cashews to finish.

Enjoy!